results.title: Medialny wizerunek walki z ubóstwem w Chinach w świetle anglo- i chińskojęzycznych publikacji China Daily 2016-2021 : analiza porównawcza

abstracts.content: 25 lutego 2021 r. Chiny oficjalnie zadeklarowały zwycięstwo w walce z ubóstwem wdrażanej w latach 2012-2020, czyli pokonanie skrajnej biedy na terenie swojego kraju. Propagowanie tego osiągnięcia w społeczności międzynarodowej stało się ważnym elementem dyplomacji publicznej Chin, w której media i możliwość przekazu określonych treści za ich pośrednictwem, odgrywają kluczową rolę. W artykule są przedstawione wyniki porównawczej analizy zawartości anglo- i chińskojęzycznych publikacji na temat chińskiego programu walki z ubóstwem, opublikowanych w latach 2016-2021 w portalu Chinadaily.com.cn, który jest największym anglojęzycznym portalem informacyjnym w Chinach. Wyniki przeprowadzonego badania pokazują różne strategie przyjęte przez redakcję China Daily w odniesieniu do audytorium zagranicznego i chińskiego oraz pozwalają na rekonstrukcję obrazu walki z ubóstwem, który Chiny chcą przekazać światu za pośrednictwem mediów.

On February 25, 2021, China officially declared victory in the fight against poverty, which means that extreme poverty has been overcome in China. Correspondingly propagating this achievement in the international community has become an important element of China's public diplomacy, in which media and the possibility of conveying specific content through them played a key role. The article presents the results of a comparative content analysis of English and Chinese-language publications about Chinese fight against poverty, published in the years 2016-2021 on Chinadaily.com.cn, which is the largest English-language information portal in China. The results of the research show the different strategies adopted by the editorial board of China Daily towards the foreign and Chinese audiences, and the reconstructive image of the fight against poverty, which China wants to convey to the world through the media.

abstracts.content: Zrównoważony rozwój nie jest jednym z wyraźnie uznanych celów postępowań upadłościowych, chociaż interes społeczny jest w znacznym stopniu obecny w ich podstawowych funkcjach polegających na zapewnieniu sprawiedliwego podziału między wierzycieli lub restrukturyzacji przedsiębiorstw znajdujących się w trudnej sytuacji, ale mających szansę na utrzymanie. W rozdziale omówiono kilka konkretnych przykładów sytuacji, w których postępowanie upadłościowe przyczynia się do osiągnięcia celów środowiskowych, społecznych, etycznych oraz związanych z ładem korporacyjnym (ESG/ESEG). Autor nie popiera postulatu dodania do prawa upadłościowego wyraźnego odniesienia do celów zrównoważonego rozwoju, ponieważ stwierdzono, że postępowanie upadłościowe może lepiej przyczynić się do realizacji tych celów, pozostając w ramach swoich obecnych funkcji, zwłaszcza jeśli wyniki sprzyjające zrównoważonemu rozwojowi są wspierane przez ogólne preferencje uczestników rynku, a ich osiąganie jest wspierane lub wymagane przez ogólne, pozaupadłościowe ramy prawne.

Sustainability is not among expressly acknowledged objectives of insolvency proceedings, although societal interest is present to a considerable extent within their core functions of providing equitable distribution among creditors or restructuring viable enterprises in distress. Several specific examples of situations are discussed where insolvency proceedings contribute to reaching environmental, social, ethical and governance (ESEG/ESG) goals. In conclusion the proposal to add explicit reference to sustainability objectives to insolvency laws is not supported, as it is found that insolvency proceedings might contribute better to the realisation of those objectives by staying within their current roles, especially if sustainability-enhancing outcomes are supported by general preferences of market participants and encouraged or required by the general (non-insolvency) legal framework.

abstracts.content: The aim of this text is to analyze the Polish cookbook from 1868 by Lucyna Ćwierczakiewiczowa in terms of French borrowings in the names of dishes. The analysis of the material allows us to conclude that some French borrowings are attested for the first time in the history of the Polish language in this cookbook by Lucyna Ćwierczakiewiczowa. These borrowings spread very quickly in Polish, because her cookbooks had many editions in high numbers of copies and were in common use.

results.title: "Donner un spectacle nouveau" : język francuski w teatrze jezuickim na przykładzie prologu tragedii "Josephus venditus" (1693) ojca Le Jay'a

abstracts.content: The aim of this article is to analyze the presence of the French language in the 17th-century Jesuit theater on the example of the prologue of tragedy written by Father Le Jay, entitled "Joseph venditus" (1693). The dramatic work of the Jesuit fathers is still a little researched phenomenon, at the same time its scale and scope are undeniable in the history of the Jesuit theater. Initially, texts tailored to the didactic purposes, were written only in Latin in order to enable the students of colleges to improve their skills in the use of the Cicero language. However, socio-cultural changes gradually influenced Jesuit didactics as well - French was more and more eagerly welcomed within the walls of colleges. A sign of these changes was the translation into French of the Latin original of the play "Joseph venditus". In the prologue to the tragedy, the author explains his choice by referring to the rhetorical gimmick of prosopopoeia. On stage, he shows two Geniuses - French and Latin. Their quarrel and the use of arguments in it perfectly illustrate the process that was taking place in the Jesuit theater at that time in terms of the choice of language.

abstracts.content:
The question of rhytm : Henri Meschonnic and Henri Michaux
The purpose of this article is to return to the question of rhythm, which seems to me to be fundamental to both theoretical reflection and the interpretative practice of literary discourse. Henri Mechonnic’s theory of rhythm finds an interesting literary and artistic exemplification in the article « Le rythme et le poème chez Henri Michaux ». The first part of this exemplification concerns rhythm, which in Michaux’s work is realised as an allegory of rhythm and the rhythm of his own allegory ».

abstracts.content: Muzea coraz bardziej zobligowane są do uwzględniania oczekiwań interesariuszy. Nie działają bowiem dla siebie, ale powinny być "dla kogoś". To pokazuje znaczenie budowania relacji z interesariuszami, którzy odbierają dostarczaną wartość oraz mogą uczestniczyć w procesie jej tworzenia. Tematyka interesariuszy muzeów w literaturze najczęściej obejmuje osoby odwiedzające. Podobnie wygląda to w przypadku współtworzenia wartości, rozpatrywanego głównie z perspektywy odbiorcy i końcowego etapu działań. Dlatego celem badania była identyfikacja i eksploracja roli jednej z grup interesariuszy – stowarzyszeń lokalnych i tematycznych – w procesie współtworzenia wartości. Wyniki wykazały dynamikę relacji między muzeum a interesariuszami oraz zmienność istotności interesariuszy. Zależy ona od realizowanego w danym momencie zadania i obszaru współtworzenia wartości.

Museums are increasingly obliged to take into account stakeholders’ expectations. They do not operate solely for themselves but should exist "for someone". This underscores the importance of building relationships with stakeholders, who not only receive value but also participate in its creation. In the literature, the discussion of museum stakeholders primarily focuses on visitors. Similarly, value co-creation is often considered mainly from the recipients’ perspective, particularly at the final stage of activities. Therefore, the study aimed to identify and explore the role of one stakeholder group – local and thematic associations – in the value co-creation process. The results revealed the dynamics of the relationship between the museum and its stakeholders, as well as the variability of stakeholder salience, which depends on the specific task at hand and the area of value co-creation.

Measurement of the Z boson invisible width at $\sqrt{s}$ =13 TeV with the ATLAS detector

journal.title: Physics Letters, Section B: Nuclear, Elementary Particle and High-Energy Physics

abstracts.content: A measurement of the invisible width of the Z boson using events with jets and missing transverse momentum is presented using 37 fb$^{-1}$ of 13 TeV proton–proton data collected by the ATLAS detector in 2015 and 2016. The ratio of Z $\to$ inv to Z $\to \ell\ell$ events, where inv refers to non-detected particles and ℓ is either an electron or a muon, is measured and corrected for detector effects. Events with at least one energetic central jet with $p_{T} \geq$ 110 GeV are selected for both the Z $\to$ inv and Z $\to \ell\ell$ final states to obtain a similar phase space in the ratio. The invisible width is measured to be 506 $\pm$ 2 (stat.) $\pm$ 12 (syst.) MeV and is the single most precise recoil-based measurement. The result is in agreement with the most precise determination from LEP and the Standard Model prediction based on three neutrino generations.

abstracts.content: Harshdev Madhav (b. 1954) is a Sanskrit writer from Gujarat. His poetry is innovative and modernized, often exploiting new themes and genres, unknown for classical Sanskrit literary production. Among the poems of Madhav one can find compositions in the form that brings to mind both Indian visual poetry called citrakāvya and western concrete poems. The article presents selected examples of Madhav’s visual compositions and analyses them from the point of their form and meaning. Moreover, the author investigates the matter of translation of visual poetry and difficulties of such an endeavor.

abstracts.content:
Układ celny między Księstwem Liechtensteinu a Konfederacją Szwajcarską został zawarty w 1923 r. w określonych warunkach polityki międzynarodowej w Europie. Po wojennej porażce Austro-Węgier Księstwo zostało zmuszone do rewizji swojej polityki zagranicznej kierując się w stronę Szwajcarii.
Porozumienie z 1923 r. było baza do rozwoju dalszych pogłębionych kontaktów, dziś jest ich ponad 110. Obie strony są zadowolone z tej kooperacji, szwajcarska "opieka" nad Liechtensteinem nie jest niczym nowym w Europie, ponieważ tego rodzaju kontakty (polityczne, gospodarcze i dyplomatyczne) cechują inne mikropaństwa. 
Powiązania ze Szwajcarią są uzupełniane przez członkostwo Księstwa w EOG, dające możliwość m.in. korzystania w przepływu pracowników, co jest istotne z punktu widzenia gospodarki Liechtensteinu. Bliskie kontakty z Helwecją będą kontynuowane gdyż jest to żywotny interes podalpejskiego mikropaństwa.

The customs treaty between the Principality of Liechtenstein and the Swiss Confederation was concluded in 1923 under certain conditions of international politics in Europe. After the wartime defeat of Austria-Hungary, the Principality was forced to revise its foreign policy heading towards Switzerland.
The 1923 agreement was the basis for the development of further in-depth contacts, today there are more than 110. Both sides are satisfied with this cooperation, Swiss 'care' for Liechtenstein is nothing new in Europe, as such contacts (political, economic and diplomatic) characterise other micro-states.
Ties with Switzerland are complemented by the Principality's membership of the EEA, giving it the possibility, among other things, to benefit from the movement of workers, which is important for Liechtenstein's economy. Close links with Helvetia will continue as this is a vital interest for the sub-Alpine micro-state.

results.title: Monstrancja z lwowskiego kościoła Matki Boskiej Śnieżnej : nieznane dzieło lwowskich złotników

abstracts.content: In the parish church dedicated to the Assumption of the Blessed Virgin Mary in Nowe Sioło, there is a monstrance, wchich according to oral history, is the one donated by Archbishop Wacław Hieronim Sierakowski to Latin Cathedral in Lviv in connection with the coronation of the miraculous image of Our Lady of Grace (called Domagaliczowska) in 1776. However, the inscription on the base of the monstrance dispels all doubts as to the origin: "This Monstrance of the Church of THE VIRGIN MARY, weighing 20 1/2 eighth silver, made by J. x. Kazim. Provost Wierzbicki". The goldsmith's work comes from the church of Our Lady of the Snows on Krakowskie Przedmieście (Krakow suburb) in Lviv, funded by the parish priest, Father Kazimierz Wierzbicki. The monstrance was previously considered non-existent in the literature. However, artisticly the work funded by Wierzbicki remains isolated compared to the preserved 18th-century monstrances from the Ruthenian Voivodeship. Its particular value is its crowning point in the form of a figurine of the Virgin Mary with clearly geometrical robes, whose style seems to refer to the so-called Lviv rococo sculpture. As it turns out, the monstrance from the Lviv collegiate church, previously known only as an item in the inventory, has not only survived, but is also an interesting example of a goldsmith's work incorporating artistic solutions from the field of sculpture.

results.title: Observation of quantum entanglement with top quarks at the ATLAS detector

abstracts.content: Entanglement is a key feature of quantum mechanics, with applications in fields such as metrology, cryptography, quantum information and quantum computation. It has been observed in a wide variety of systems and length scales, ranging from the microscopic to the macroscopic. However, entanglement remains largely unexplored at the highest accessible energy scales. Here we report the highest-energy observation of entanglement, in top–antitop quark events produced at the Large Hadron Collider, using a proton–proton collision dataset with a centre-of-mass energy of $\sqrt{s}$ = 13 TeV and an integrated luminosity of 140 inverse femtobarns (fb)$^{−1}$ recorded with the ATLAS experiment. Spin entanglement is detected from the measurement of a single observable D, inferred from the angle between the charged leptons in their parent top- and antitop-quark rest frames. The observable is measured in a narrow interval around the top–antitop quark production threshold, at which the entanglement detection is expected to be significant. It is reported in a fiducial phase space defined with stable particles to minimize the uncertainties that stem from the limitations of the Monte Carlo event generators and the parton shower model in modelling top-quark pair production. The entanglement marker is measured to be D = -0.537 $\pm$ 0.002(stat.) $\pm$ 0.019(syst.) for 340 GeV < m$_{t\bar{t}}$ < 380 GeV. The observed result is more than five standard deviations from a scenario without entanglement and hence constitutes the first observation of entanglement in a pair of quarks and the highest-energy observation of entanglement so far.

results.title: Propaganda komunistyczna w filmie historycznym okresu stalinowskiego na Węgrzech : postacie Maćka Gęsiarka, Sándora Petőfiego i Jánosa Bornemisszy jako przykłady upolitycznienia kina

abstracts.content:
After the Second World War, Hungarian cinematography was completely controlled by
the communist authorities. The film industry was nationalized to indoctrinate society
in the whole country. When Mátyás Rákosi served as General Secretary of the Hunga-
rian Communist Party, the main goal of cinematography was to convey the propaganda
content of the political system. This also applied to historical films in which national
symbols and great figures were used to appropriate the space of history, the national
liberation struggle, the fight for the nation›s freedom. In my study, I analyze selected
historical films of the socialist realism period in Hungary in terms of plot strategies and
film language. I am pointing to the means used that served the propaganda purposes of
the communist authorities. I emphasize the fact that even the figures of romantic heroes,
such as Sándor Petőfi , could be effectively used in a political context and, unlike pictures
addressing current problems, historical films were much more visually attractive.

results.title: Refleksja o muzyce żydowskiej na łamach polsko-żydowskiego dziennika "Chwila"

abstracts.content: Polsko-żydowski dziennik „Chwila”, wydawany Lwowie w latach 1919–1939, był organem prasowym o profilu syjonistycznym, docierającym tak do środowiska żydowskiego, jak i polskiego. To opiniotwórcze czasopismo udostępniało swoje łamy wpływowym żydowskim pisarzom, jak Icchok Lejb Perec czy Herman Hesse, prowadziło również obszerne rubryki poświęcone krytyce literackiej, teatralnej, muzycznej i plastycznej, dzięki czemu stanowi dziś wartościowe źródło dla badaczy historii idei i sztuki. Wśród prominentnych krytyków udzielali się w „Chwili” m.in. Henryk Herscheles (od 1931 roku redaktor naczelny czasopisma) oraz Alfred Plohn (szef jej działu muzycznego i aktywny organizator lwowskiego życia kulturalnego). Głos miało tam również młode pokolenie recenzentów, wśród których wyróżniała się Zofia Lissa. Niniejszy artykuł omawia teksty krytycznomuzyczne i teoretyczne poświęcone muzyce żydowskiej, które ukazały się w „Chwili” w dwudziestoleciu międzywojennym. Ich twórcami byli zarówno pisarze związani ze Lwowem (Plohn, Lissa), jak i autorzy zagraniczni, którzy nadsyłali do Lwowa swoje korespondencje lub których teksty tłumaczono ze względu na ich wysoką wartość poznawczą. Wśród głównych zagadnień podejmowanych w analizowanych w niniejszym artykule pracach znalazły się: definicja i istota muzyki żydowskiej, działalność kompozytorów żydowskiego pochodzenia, „żydowskość” kompozytorów i jej przejawy, nowa muzyka żydowska (reprezentowana przez przedstawicieli tzw. „nowej szkoły żydowskiej w muzyce” oraz nurt nowohebrajski), badania nad muzyką żydowską (historia i źródła). Zrekonstruowane i omówione tu piśmiennictwo pozwala rozpoznać zaplecze intelektualne i ideowe jego twórców, a także zaznajomić się z najważniejszymi dyskusjami o muzyce żydowskiej, które toczono w środowisku lwowskich Żydów w odnośnym czasie.

The Polish-Jewish daily “Chwila”, published in Lviv in the years 1919–1939, was a Zionist press organ, reaching both the Jewish and Polish circles. This opinion-forming magazine made its columns available to influential Jewish writers, such as Isaac Leib Peretz or Hermann Hesse, and also ran extensive columns devoted to literary, theater, music and art criticism, thanks to which it is today a valuable source for researchers of the history of ideas and art. Among the prominent critics who contributed to “Chwila”, we can mention, among others: Henryk Herscheles (from 1931 editor-in-chief of the magazine) and Alfred Plohn (head of its music department and active organizer of Lviv’s cultural life). The young generation of reviewers also had a voice there, among whom Zofia Lissa stood out. This article discusses critical and theoretical texts on Jewish music published in “Chwila” in the interwar period. Their creators were both writers associated with Lviv (Plohn, Lissa) and foreign authors who sent their correspondence to Lviv or whose texts were translated due to their high substantive value. Among the main issues addressed in the works analyzed in this paper were: the definition and essence of Jewish music, the activity of composers of Jewish origin, the “Jewishness” of composers and its manifestations, new Jewish music (represented by representatives of the so-called “new Jewish school in music” and the new-Hebrew direction), research on Jewish music (its history and sources). The literature reconstructed and discussed here allows to recognize the intellectual and ideological background of its creators, as well as to familiarize oneself with the most important discussions about Jewish music that took place in the Lviv Jewish community at the relevant time.

The article is an attempt to show the successes and failures of the State Police related to the organization's practice of suppressing people's mass demonstrations in 1930-1935. The first part of the text briefly describes the general situation of the State Police in the studied period, while the second part shows the general scheme of the police's actions against people's mass demonstrations. The number of State Police interventions in 1930-1935 is presented in the context of the general phenomenon of social revolt. In this way, it became possible to attempt to determine the scale of the actions taken by the police.

results.title: How Universities and NGOs collaborate

abstracts.content: Non-governmental organisations (NGOs) differ from universities in many aspects, including those concerning organisational culture, values and ways of functioning. With this in mind, the aim of this chapter is to present the specific nature of collaboration between universities and NGOs regarding the implementation of the third mission of the university sector. The paper examines the existing cooperation typologies of universities–non-governmental organisations (UNI-NGOs). Taking into account changes in the environment and emerging social challenges, the evolution of UNI-NGOs is also described considering the actors, fields and methods of collaboration involved. The factors influencing this institutional cooperation are also presented.

abstracts.content:
Murder in the Cathedral (1935) was the first and most successful play in
which T.S. Eliot brought back poetry to the stage. His wholehearted commitment to both poetry and theatrical performance made Eliot combine them in the
form of verse drama, once popular, but in the 20th century apparently eclipsed
by modernity. Eliot was deeply convinced that the restoration of poetry in drama
intensifies the dramatic situation and as a result it increases the theatrical effect.
Consequently, he believed that there are certain situations and experiences which
cannot be adequately communicated to the audience in the language of prose.
When themes which the playwright attempts to handle touch upon the ineffable,
poetic expression is the only viable solution. The article looks upon Murder in the
Cathedral as a metaphysical drama, with its central theme revolving around
the reflection upon the existential condition of man and of the world viewed from
the Christian perspective. The underlying assumption is that for such theme verse
drama seems the most appropriate poetic strategy. The article also proposes to
examine how various streaks of Eliot’s life and creative output converge in the
thematic and dramatic focus of the play. The most conspicuous among them
are: elements and echoes of ancient Greek drama, aspects of Christian liturgy,
historical facts with their basis in relevant documents, and references to the
Gospels. Bishop Becket and the Chorus emerge as the two main protagonists of
the play representing the depth of religious reflection and psychological truth.

results.title: Adam Mickiewicz’s "Pan Tadeusz" in the Hebrew translation by Yosef Lixṭenbom : some rendering difficulties and solutions

abstracts.content: Yosef Lixṭenbom translated the poem "Pan Tadeusz" by Adam Mickiewicz into Hebrew. This paper investigates the ways in which Lixṭenbom copes with the names of “realia”. It turns out that his prevalent method was to use a more general term than the one appearing in the source. The effect is a somewhat vague style. The second dominant strategy is to find an approximate equivalent in the target culture. This leads to the effect of “domestication”.

results.title: Reportage from the (post-)contact zone : Polish travellers to decolonised India (1950-1980)

abstracts.content: The texts analysed in this chapter span the first three decades of India’s independence. Polish reporters document both the change that occurred in postcolonial India, and the lingering effects of foreign rule on society and culture of the Subcontinent. It is a former contact zone, a post-contact zone, where the former colonisers are absent but their presence can still be felt. Polish reporters visiting India in the 1950s and early 1960s, such as Witold Koehler, Jerzy Ros and Wiesław Górnicki often voice their critique of British colonialism, especially as (semi-official) representatives of a communist state, the Polish People’s Republic. In their accounts, they mention clubs allowing entry only to foreigners, the conflicts stirred by the colonial administration, lasting longer than the British rule, the greed of industrialists and the oppression of peasants. The reporters underline their anti-colonial viewpoint, but in many situations, they are trapped in the convention of colonial relations. Thus, the main question is whether reporters from socialist Poland can truly be anti-colonial, and, given their own dependence from the Soviet Union, can they be anti-imperialist?

abstracts.content: The scientific description of translation as a creative act belongs to most important subjects triggering the development of the translatological research. In this paper, we present an overview of the scientific achievements of Paul Kußmaul, a German theoretician and didactician of translation, one of the pioneers of scientific research on creative aspects of the translation process. The main focus of attention lies on the evolution of the views of the researcher, as well as his attempt to develop a scientifically grounded model of translation as a creative act, referring to three aspects of creativity: inventiveness, adequacy and acceptability.

abstracts.content: Sofia Svechina i Sofia Rostopchina były XIX-wiecznymi rosyjskimi arystokratkami, które nawróciły się na katolicyzm. Svechina po nawróceniu w 1816 roku wyjechała do Paryża. Prowadziła tam salon, do którego uczęszczali wybitni myśliciele literaccy i religijni. Sofia Rostopchina po przeprowadzce do Paryża w 1817 roku poślubiła Eugène de Ségur. Dopiero w wieku 57 lat zwróciła się ku fikcji i stała się sławną autorką powieści i bajek dla dzieci. Ten artykuł pokazuje, jak wybory religijne Swiechiny i Rostopchiny wpłynęły na ich życie.

Sofia Svechina and Sofia Rostopczyna were nineteenth-century Russian aristocrats and converts to Catholicism. Svechina, after her conversion in 1816, went to Paris. There she ran a salon frequented by prominent literary and religious thinkers. Sofia Rostopchina after moving to Paris in 1817, married Eugène de Ségur. It was not until she was 57 that she turned to fiction and became a famous author of novels and fairy tales for children. This paper shows how the religious choices of Svechina and Rostopczynej influenced their lives.

results.title: Znacie? To posłuchajcie : czyli o miejscu streszczenia w kulturze operowej

abstracts.content: Streszczenie to zjawisko towarzyszące operze przez całą jej historię i bardzo długo (w związku z problemami ze zrozumiałością tekstu śpiewanego) używane za nieodzowne uzupełnienie spektaklu, rzadko jednak stanowiące przedmiot namysłu badawczego. Artykuł poświęcony jest różnym funkcjom i typom streszczeń operowych: streszczeniu zintegrowanemu ze spektaklem ("Oedipus Rex" Strawińskiego i Cocteau), streszczeniom o charakterze encyklopedycznym oraz streszczeniom funkcjonalnym, powstałym na potrzeby konkretnych spektakli operowych.

Summary is a phenomenon accompanying opera throughout its history and for a long time (due to the difficulty of understanding the text of the songs), was used as an indispensable complement to the show, yet rarely subjected to analysis by researchers. The article is devoted to the variety of functions and types of opera summaries: integrated with the show ("Oedipus Rex" by Igor Strawiński and Jean Cocteau), encyclopaedic and functional, the latter created to serve the needs of specific opera performances.

book.title: Activism in hard times in Central and Eastern Europe : people power

results.title: Polarization as driver and barrier to civic activism

abstracts.content: This chapter considers how political and social polarization has affected divisions within civil society and activists’ responses. Some of the polarization that plagues so many societies in Central and Eastern Europe (CEE) can be traced to the effective populist rhetoric of their political leaders. These divisions have also been exacerbated by social media. We first profile a well-known Hungarian activist representing Hungarian Environmental Partnership Foundation who addresses polarization among civic actors by establishing bridges among generations of activists and organizations that share similar goals. Our second activist from Poland is a representative of Odra-Niemen Association, which works on historical remembrance, patriotism, and responsibility for places of historical importance and takes apolitical approach to its own mission. The aim of the chapter is to examine different responses to the problem of polarization among CEE activists who then apply various tactics to build bridges among divided groups, engaging citizens in dialogue and cooperation.

results.title: Remittances : immigrant entrepreneurs and their impact on the home-country economy

abstracts.content: The literature on international migration has presented remittances as one of the key drivers of economic change: these flows can generate economic growth and contribute to poverty reduction. But how can remittances affect the home-country economy and entrepreneurship activities? Based on the sheer magnitude of such flows, remittances should impact business creation through two major channels. First, they could provide financial incentives for starting and developing firms in one’s home country. Second, the savings from remittances are channelled to official financial institutions; they enhance access to credit for future and current entrepreneurs. The main findings from the literature review indicate that the effect of remittances on business creation and development is at best mixed. Yet, there are alternative channels through which immigrant entrepreneurs can contribute to the development of their countries of origin. The first one is transnational immigrant entrepreneurship: many immigrants can develop personal business ties between host and home countries and initiate business activities. Secondly, there are social remittances: migrants who become entrepreneurs can also transfer their business ideas and encourage business activities amongst friends and family members who stay in their home country. This chapter analyses all of these channels for possible entrepreneurial development in the home-country economy from both a theoretical and empirical perspective.
